<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>31-5603.01</num>
  <heading>Registration requirement.</heading>
  <text>No person shall offer or sell a security in the District unless the security is registered under this chapter, the security or transaction is exempt under <cite path="§31-5604.01">§ 31-5604.01</cite> or <cite path="§31-5604.02">§ 31-5604.02</cite>, or the security is a federal covered security.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 13-203" type="History" path="§301">Oct. 26, 2000, D.C. Law 13-203, § 301, 47 DCR 7837</annotation>
    <annotation type="Editor's Notes">Section 806 of <cite doc="D.C. Law 13-203">D.C. Law 13-203</cite> provided: “Titles III and IV shall apply as of June 1, 2001.”</annotation>
    <annotation type="Section References">This section is referenced in <cite path="§31-5603.08">§ 31-5603.08</cite>, <cite path="§31-5604.01">§ 31-5604.01</cite>, <cite path="§31-5604.02">§ 31-5604.02</cite>, <cite path="§31-5604.03">§ 31-5604.03</cite>, <cite path="§31-5604.04">§ 31-5604.04</cite>, <cite path="§31-5605.01">§ 31-5605.01</cite>, <cite path="§31-5606.05">§ 31-5606.05</cite>, and <cite path="§31-5608.01">§ 31-5608.01</cite>.</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>
